  "prompt": "What is a good website for free books?",
  "response": "There are several websites where you can find free books. Here are a few popular options:\n\n1. **Project Gutenberg**: Offers over 60,000 free eBooks, primarily consisting of classic literature that is in the public domain.\n\n2. **Open Library**: An initiative of the Internet Archive, it provides access to millions of free eBooks, including classic and contemporary works. You can borrow eBooks if you create a free account.\n\n3. **Google Books**: While not all of the books are free, many classic texts can be accessed for free, and you can often find previews or excerpts of current books.\n\n4. **ManyBooks**: Features a large collection of free eBooks, with a focus on older works and independent authors.\n\n5. **LibriVox**: While primarily an audiobook platform, LibriVox offers free audiobooks of public domain texts, which can be a great way to enjoy literature.\n\n6. **Smashwords**: A platform for independent authors, where many offer their works for free alongside paid options.\n\nMake sure to check the copyright details of each book to ensure that it is available for free distribution.",
